My great uncle (RIP)'s hobby was to just sit outside shirtless at summer noon under his grape vines' shadow and tinker with various metal gadgets for a few hours, welding, hammering various pieces together, wrenching bolts. God knows none of it was useful. Good way to spend time.

Ideal lifestyle is this, but whittling wooden statuettes or doing other craftsmanship type activity like bending nails into shapes. No need to use mere practicality as an excuse to sit in the sun's hours.

Step 1: Obtain land/garden
Step 2: Plant grape vines and pull them into an arc/roofed cabana structure
Step 3: Sit under it at 11:30
Step 4: make a bunch of these and give them to your friends and strangers you meet
